y for rheumatism.</unittitle><container id="aspace_66ae95eabcba5f09caac41a467acc4e2" label="Mixed Materials" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_7b535246e07a4f9cda662c8896a360c6" level="item"><did><unittitle>Note giving birth day of the three Silver Children (1857, 1861 [?], 1863).</unittitle><container id="aspace_b2ece8c6b9b563d690ed56ddbc0a8c19" label="Mixed Materials" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_46ed4ee338e0f9dacf8b5371cbc5734c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Treasurer's book of Local Assembly No. 406; 4 pp. only filled. (This organization was the local of the glass bottle workers' union, National Trade Assembly #143 of the Knights of Labor. Pertinent corres. and Xeroxes from selected pp. of <title>Proceedings</title> on file in this folder.)</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="approximate" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1890-02/1890-12" type="inclusive">Feb.-Dec. 1890</unitdate><container id="aspace_a21405dd3bc41bed5d34fe7d88d6196a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_10c512ca12038b0286a3ff646ed7f69b" parent="aspace_a21405dd3bc41bed5d34fe7d88d6196a" type="volume">13</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_7087c471218345a79e54f5c970548c0b" level="item"><did><unittitle>Payment vouchers (61 items, Nos. 25-85) authorizing Silver, as treasurer of the organization, to pay stated sum to a certain person, in most cases, George P. Pierce.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1890-02-18/1891-07-07" type="inclusive">Feb. 18, 1890-July 7, 1891</unitdate><container id="aspace_b35865bbd08703c2b9a4e3fcb6a888c1" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_93e6450c21a60d3eaea9bec611107a43" parent="aspace_b35865bbd08703c2b9a4e3fcb6a888c1" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_65c85852402f281e7a1e5316fb994282" level="item"><did><unittitle>4 loose sheets of calculati